# Feature PM (per-feature artifacts)
# Track planning artifacts (REQUEST/PRD/BLUEPRINT/tasks.sql/coverage.json/STATE.md);
# ignore large/regenerable per-task context bundles and operational journals.
features/*/journal.md
features/*/tasks/*/context.md
# Keep the documentation example fully checked in.
!features/example-pm-dryrun/journal.md
!features/example-pm-dryrun/tasks/*/context.md

# ── Local AI-assisted maintainer workflow ──────────────────────────────
# The following paths describe the maintainer's personal setup for using
# AI coding assistants (agent definitions, skills, session hooks, prompt
# templates, PM-flow planning artifacts, agents.md spec files, etc.).
# They are not required to build, test, or contribute to Toaster — if you
# want to plug in your own AI tooling you are welcome to, this is just
# one way of doing it. The public-facing convention files (CI workflows,
# PR/issue templates, repo actions) remain tracked.
.github/agents/
.github/skills/
.github/hooks/
.github/instructions/
.github/prompts/
.github/registry/
.github/templates/
.github/copilot-instructions.md

# agents.md convention files (AI coding assistants — nearest-file wins)
/AGENTS.md
/src/AGENTS.md
/src-tauri/AGENTS.md

# Per-feature planning artifacts (maintainer's PRD/Blueprint/tasks flow)
/features/
